9998499, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://public.com/stocks/o/forecast-price-target', 'title': 'O Stock Forecast: Analyst Ratings, Predictions & Price Target 2026', 'content': "## O Analyst Ratings\n\n#### Bulls say\n\nRealty Income's positive outlook is supported by its substantial portfolio of approximately 15,500 properties across diverse sectors, bolstered by recent expansions into industrial, gaming, and other properties contributing to 20% of revenue. The company has demonstrated improved financial flexibility with a lower cost of debt and a notable increase in acquisition-driven earnings potential, as evidenced by its $6.2 billion in closed transactions in 2025 along with enhanced investment selectivity. Furthermore, the rise in stock price, alongside normalization of transaction volumes, positions Realty Income advantageously for future growth, particularly in an increasingly favorable acquisition environment in Europe.\n\n#### Bears say [...] Order type\n\nBuy in\n\nOrder amount\n\nEst. shares\n\n0 shares\n\n## FAQs About Realty Income Corp (O) Forecast\n\n### What is the analyst rating for O?\n\n### Should I buy or sell O stock?\n\n### What is the analyst price target for O?\n\n### What is the 2026 price prediction for O?\n\nRealty Income Corp (O)\n\n## O Analyst Forecast & Price Prediction\n\n## Start investing in O\n\nOrder type\n\nBuy in\n\nOrder amount\n\nEst. shares\n\n0 shares\n\n© Copyright 2026 Public Holdings, Inc. All Rights Reserved.\n\nMarket data powered by Xignite. [...] #### Bears say\n\nThe negative outlook on Realty Income's stock is primarily influenced by challenges in sourcing sufficient and accretive acquisitions, which may hinder revenue growth. Additionally, rising interest rates above market expectations, alongside risks related to tenant bankruptcies and subsequent loss of net operating income (NOI), raise concerns about the company's ability to maintain its dividend payouts. Furthermore, the inherent credit risk associated with their tenant base and the vulnerability to inflation pressures signify broader economic uncertainties, which could adversely impact their financial stability in the long run.\n\n## O Analyst Forecast & Price Prediction\n\n## Start investing in O\n\nOrder type\n\nBuy in\n\nOrder amount\n\nEst. shares\n\n0 shares", 'score': 0.9998118, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/O/', 'title': 'Realty Income Corporation (O) Stock Price, News, Quote & History', 'content': "FY25\n\nQ2\n\nFY25\n\nQ3\n\nFY25\n\nQ4\n\nFY25\n\n0\n\n500M\n\n1B\n\nView More\n\n### Analyst Insights: O\n\nView More \n\n### Analyst Price Targets\n\n60.00\n\n67.85 Average\n\n60.95 Current\n\n75.00 High\n\n### Analyst Recommendations\n\n### Latest Rating\n\nDate 3/17/2026\n\nAnalyst Evercore ISI Group\n\nRating Action Maintains\n\nRating In-Line\n\nPrice Action Raises\n\nPrice Target 65 -> 67\n\nView More\n\n### Statistics: O\n\nView More \n\n### Valuation Measures\n\nAs of 3/20/2026\n\n Market Cap\n\n  56.83B\n Enterprise Value\n\n  85.74B\n Trailing P/E\n\n  52.09\n Forward P/E\n\n  38.02\n PEG Ratio (5yr expected)\n\n  --\n Price/Sales (ttm)\n\n  9.63\n Price/Book (mrq)\n\n  1.44\n Enterprise Value/Revenue\n\n  14.91\n Enterprise Value/EBITDA\n\n  17.92\n\n### Financial Highlights\n\n#### Profitability and Income Statement\n\n Profit Margin\n\n  18.37%\n Return on Assets (ttm) [...] Realty Income Corporation, an S&P 500 company, is real estate partner to the world's leading companies. We serve our clients as a full-service real estate capital provider. As of December 31, 2025, we have a portfolio of over 15,500 properties in all 50 states of the United States (U.S.), the United Kingdom (U.K.), and eight other countries in Europe. We are known as (The Monthly Dividend Company) and have a mission to invest in people and places to deliver dependable monthly dividends that increase over time. Since our listing on the NYSE in 1994, we have had 133 dividend increases and are a member of the S&P 500 Dividend Aristocrats index for having increased our dividend for over 31 consecutive years. The firm was founded and incorporated in 1969 in Maryland, USA. [...] Realty Income Corporation (O) is forming a significant $1 billion joint venture with Apollo to diversify its funding and enhance growth. This venture will target a 500-property retail portfolio, providing Realty Income with long-term capital while retaining management rights.\n\nUpdated 4m ago · Powered by Yahoo Scout\n\n Previous Close  62.64\n Open  62.30\n Bid  61.01 x 50000\n Ask  61.49 x 110000\n Day's Range  60.60 - 62.60\n 52 Week Range  50.71 - 67.94\n Volume  10,098,046\n Avg. Volume  6,567,621\n Market Cap (intraday)  57.035B\n Beta (5Y Monthly)  0.77\n PE Ratio (TTM)  52.09\n EPS (TTM)  1.17\n Earnings Date (est.)  May 4, 2026\n Forward Dividend & Yield  3.23 (5.30%)\n Ex-Dividend Date  Mar 31, 2026\n 1y Target Est  67.85", 'score': 0.998784, 'raw_content': None}], 'response_time': 3.57, 'request_id': 'd81758f7-08c4-47ed-b716-8cb11700f0bc'}
