2026-03-27 05:36:20 | DEBUG    | src/search_service.py:300 | [Tavily] 原始响应: {'query': 'Verizon Communications Inc. earnings revenue profit growth forecast', 'follow_up_questions': None, 'answer': None, 'images': [], 'results': [{'url': 'https://finance.yahoo.com/markets/stocks/articles/verizons-business-segment-portfolio-generate-154000057.html', 'title': "Can Verizon's Business Segment Portfolio Generate Future Profit?", 'content': 'Verizon Communications Inc.’s VZ Business segment has faced a steady decline in recent years, as revenue growth from enterprise and government services has slowed. This slowdown has made it more challenging for the company to sustain growth in this segment.  \n  \nIn the latest quarter, Verizon’s business segment revenues declined to $7.4 billion, down from $7.5 billion in the same period last year. This decline is due to several factors, including strong competition from telecom, cloud and networking providers, rising operational costs and a shift by customers toward more flexible, cloud-based solutions, all of which are putting pressure on profitability.', 'score': 0.9998511, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.investing.com/news/earnings/verizon-shares-rise-as-q4-results-and-2026-outlook-top-expectations-4475643', 'title': 'Verizon shares rise as Q4 results and 2026 outlook top expectations', 'content': 'The company posted adjusted earnings per share of $1.09 for the fourth quarter, surpassing the analyst estimate of $1.06. Revenue came in at $36.4 billion, above the consensus estimate of $36.1 billion. Verizon also delivered its highest quarterly total mobility and broadband volumes since 2019, with 616,000 postpaid phone net additions.\n\nVerizon\'s wireless service revenue reached $21.0 billion in the fourth quarter, up 1.1% YoY, while wireless equipment revenue increased 9.1% YoY to $8.2 billion. The company added 372,000 broadband subscribers during the quarter, including 319,000 fixed wireless access customers and 67,000 Fios internet additions. [...] # Verizon shares rise as Q4 results and 2026 outlook top expectations\n\nBy\n\nAuthorSam Boughedda\n\nEarnings\n\nPublished 01/30/2026, 06:41 AM\n\nVerizon shares rise as Q4 results and 2026 outlook top expectations\n\nView all comments (0)0\n\n&copy; Reuters.\n\n© Reuters.\n\nVZ1.01%\n\nInvesting.com -- Verizon Communications Inc. (NYSE: VZ) reported fourth-quarter earnings and revenue that exceeded analyst expectations, while providing an upbeat outlook for 2026 that signals the beginning of a strategic turnaround. The telecommunications giant\'s shares rose 4.1% following the announcement.\n\nStay ahead of every breaking move with InvestingPro -- 55% off [...] "We are exiting 2025 with strong momentum, delivered by a team that is intensely focused on winning through healthy volumes and fiscally responsible growth," said Verizon CEO Dan Schulman. "Our performance in the fourth quarter proves that we can grow by delighting our customers and building deep trust and loyalty."\n\nLooking ahead, Verizon provided an optimistic outlook for 2026, projecting adjusted EPS of $4.90 to $4.95, well above the analyst consensus of $4.76. The company expects total retail postpaid phone net additions of 750,000 to 1.0 million and total mobility and broadband service revenue growth of 2.0% to 3.0%.', 'score': 0.99964297, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.marketbeat.com/stocks/NYSE/VZ/earnings/', 'title': 'Verizon Communications (VZ) Earnings Date and Reports 2026', 'content': "Add\n\nCompare\n\n Share\n\n Share\n\nEarnings\n\n   Stock Analysis\n   Analyst Forecasts\n   Chart\n   Competitors\n   Dividend\n   Earnings\n   Financials\n   Headlines\n   Insider Trades\n   Options Chain\n   Ownership\n   SEC Filings\n   Short Interest\n   Trends\n   Buy This Stock\n\n## Verizon Communications Earnings Summary\n\nVerizon Communications released Q4 2025 earnings on January 30, 2026, reporting an EPS of $1.09, which beat the consensus estimate of $1.06 by $0.03. Quarterly revenue rose _2.0%_ year-over-year to $36.38 billion, above the consensus estimate of $36.20 billion. With a trailing EPS of _$4.05_ and a P/E Ratio of _12.48_, Verizon Communications' earnings are expected to grow _3.62%_ next year, from $4.69 to $4.86 per share.\n\nUpcoming \n\n Earnings Date Apr. 27 Before Market Opens Estimated [...] Verizon Communications (NYSE:VZ) has a recorded annual revenue of $138.19 billion.\n\nHow much profit does Verizon Communications generate each year?\n\nVerizon Communications (NYSE:VZ) has a recorded net income of $17.17 billion. VZ has generated $4.05 earnings per share over the last four quarters.\n\nWhat is Verizon Communications' price-to-earnings ratio?\n\nVerizon Communications (NYSE:VZ) has a trailing price-to-earnings ratio of 12.50 and a forward price-to-earnings ratio of 10.79. The price/earnings-to-growth ratio is 2.12.\n\nWhat is Verizon Communications' EPS forecast for next year?\n\nVerizon Communications' earnings are expected to grow from $4.69 per share to $4.86 per share in the next year, which is a 3.62% increase.\n\n## More Earnings Resources from MarketBeat [...] | 4/22/2024 | Q1 2024 | $1.12 | $1.15 | +$0.03 | $1.21 | $33.23B | $33.00B |  |", 'score': 0.99953806, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://finance.yahoo.com/news/verizon-rides-solid-subscriber-growth-141100271.html', 'title': 'Verizon Rides on Solid Subscriber Growth: Will it Boost Revenue?', 'content': 'Verizon Communications Inc. VZ is benefiting from healthy traction in the wireless vertical backed by competitive price offers and diligent execution. In the fourth quarter, the company reported wireless retail postpaid phone gross adds of 3.5 million, up 13% year over year. Consumer postpaid phone gross adds were 2.7 million, up 15.3% year over year. It also reported 5.6 million postpaid upgrades, up 8.7% year over year. Its wireless retail postpaid ARPA was $147.36 at the end of the fourth quarter, up 1.2% year over year. [...] Verizon expects strong growth in wireless subscribers in 2026. The company expects 750,000 to 1 million postpaid phone net adds in 2026, indicating 2-3x growth compared to 2025. However, wireless service revenue growth is expected to remain flat.  \n  \nStrong network investments are supporting wireless growth. The company reports that c-band deployment is 90% complete, and investment in 5G and RAN is ongoing. Moreover, the strategy of AI integration in wireless operations to predict potential issues and optimize the overall operations is positive. [...] ## VZ’s Price Performance, Valuation and Estimates\n\nVerizon has gained 15.8% in the past year against the Wireless National industry’s decline of 4.4%.\n\nZacks Investment Research\n\nZacks Investment Research\n\n \n\nImage Source: Zacks Investment Research\n\nGoing by the price/earnings ratio, the company’s shares currently trade at 10.17, down from 13.01 for the industry.\n\nZacks Investment Research\n\nZacks Investment Research\n\n \n\nImage Source: Zacks Investment Research\n\nVZ’s earnings estimates for 2025 and 2026 have increased over the past 60 days.\n\nZacks Investment Research\n\nZacks Investment Research\n\n \n\nImage Source: Zacks Investment Research\n\nVerizon currently carries a Zacks Rank #3 (Hold). You can see the complete list of today’s Zacks #1 Rank (Strong Buy) stocks here.', 'score': 0.99923277, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.marketscreener.com/quote/stock/VERIZON-COMMUNICATIONS-IN-4830/finances/', 'title': 'Verizon Communications, Inc.: Financial Data Forecasts Estimates ...', 'content': '| Fiscal Period: December | 2021 | 2022 | 2023 | 2024 | 2025 | 2026 | 2027 | 2028 |\n ---  ---  ---  --- \n| Net sales 1 | 133,613 | 136,835 | 133,974 | 134,788 | 138,191 | 144,025 | 145,731 | 147,737 |\n| Change  2.41% | -2.09% | 0.61% | 2.52% | 4.22% | 1.18% | 1.38% |\n| EBITDA 1 | 48,380 | 47,870 | 47,789 | 48,791 | 49,997 | 53,068 | 54,510 | 56,080 |\n| Change  -1.05% | -0.17% | 2.1% | 2.47% | 6.14% | 2.72% | 2.88% |\n| EBIT 1 | 32,448 | 30,467 | 22,877 | 28,686 | 29,259 | 33,688 | 35,083 | 36,381 |\n| Change  -6.11% | -24.91% | 25.39% | 2% | 15.14% | 4.14% | 3.7% |\n| Interest Paid 1 | -3,485 | -3,613 | -5,524 | -6,649 | -6,694 | -7,512 | -7,487 | -7,494 |\n| Earnings before Tax (EBT) 1 | 29,420 | 28,271 | 16,987 | 22,979 | 22,672 | 26,558 | 27,854 | 28,941 | [...] | Earnings before Tax (EBT) 1 | 7,078 | 7,824 | 8,374 | 6,144 | 6,083 | 6,857 | 6,520 | 8,811 | 6,500 | 6,112 | 6,192 | -1,817 | 6,075 | 6,034 | 4,302 | 6,568 | 6,473 | 6,609 | 6,527 | 3,063 | 6,581 | 6,965 | 7,010 | 6,228 | 6,972 | 7,202 | 7,130 | 6,521 |\n| Change  10.54% | 7.03% | -26.63% | -0.99% | 12.72% | -4.91% | 35.14% | -26.23% | -5.97% | 1.31% | -129.34% | 434.34% | -0.67% | -28.7% | 52.67% | -1.45% | 2.1% | -1.24% | -53.07% | 114.87% | 5.83% | 0.65% | -11.16% | 11.96% | 3.28% | -0.99% | -8.54% |\n| Net income 1 | 5,245 | 5,800 | 6,407 | 4,613 | 4,580 | 5,199 | 4,900 | 6,577 | 4,909 | 4,648 | 4,762 | -2,705 | 4,602 | 4,593 | 3,306 | 5,005 | 4,879 | 5,003 | 4,950 | 2,342 | 5,055 | 5,339 | 5,364 | 4,777 | 5,362 | 5,533 | 5,462 | 4,982 | [...] | Fiscal Period: December | 2021 | 2022 | 2023 | 2024 | 2025 | 2026 | 2027 | 2028 |\n ---  ---  ---  --- \n| Profitability |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |\n ---  ---  ---  --- \n| EBITDA Margin (%) | 36.21% | 34.98% | 35.67% | 36.2% | 36.18% | 36.85% | 37.4% | 37.96% |\n| EBIT Margin (%) | 24.29% | 22.27% | 17.08% | 21.28% | 21.17% | 23.39% | 24.07% | 24.63% |\n| EBT Margin (%) | 22.02% | 20.66% | 12.68% | 17.05% | 16.41% | 18.44% | 19.11% | 19.59% |\n| Net margin (%) | 16.51% | 15.53% | 8.67% | 12.99% | 12.43% | 14.03% | 14.42% | 14.93% |\n| FCF margin (%) | 14.41% | 10.27% | 13.96% | 14.71% | 14.56% | 14.7% | 15.21% | 15.94% |\n| FCF / Net Income (%) | 87.26% | 66.12% | 161.08% | 113.23% | 117.19% | 104.81% | 105.54% | 106.79% |\n| Profitability |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |', 'score': 0.9988927, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://finance.yahoo.com/news/verizon-surpasses-q4-earnings-estimates-145900018.html', 'title': 'Verizon Surpasses Q4 Earnings Estimates on Healthy Revenue ...', 'content': '5 min read\n\nVZ\n\n+1.01%\n\nANET\n\n-3.70%\n\nPINS\n\n+0.11%\n\nVerizon Communications Inc. VZ recorded solid fourth-quarter 2025 results with healthy wireless traction and fiber densification. Both adjusted earnings and revenues beat the respective Zacks Consensus Estimate, with the company delivering on its 2025 guidance.   \n  \nThe company registered solid broadband growth with total fixed wireless access net additions of 319,000, growing the subscriber base to nearly 5.7 million. The company remains well poised to achieve its target of 8 to 9 million fixed wireless access subscribers by 2028.\n\n## Net Income [...] ### Verizon Communications Inc. Price, Consensus and EPS Surprise\n\nVerizon Communications Inc. price-consensus-eps-surprise-chart | Verizon Communications Inc. Quote\n\n## Revenues\n\nQuarterly total operating revenues improved 2% to $36.38 billion with higher wireless equipment revenues driven by targeted pricing actions, customer growth, sales of perks and add-on services and growth in fixed wireless access. The top line beat the consensus estimate of $35.94 billion. For 2025, Verizon recorded total revenues of $138.19 billion, up 2.5% year over year.\n\n## Quarterly Segment Results [...] Consumer: Total revenues from this segment improved 3.2% year over year to $28.44 billion with growth across all businesses. Service revenues were up 0.9% to $20.25 billion, while wireless equipment revenues improved 9.6% to $7.11 billion. Other revenues totaled $1.08 billion, up 6.6% year over year.  \n  \nWireless retail postpaid churn was 1.21%, while retail postpaid phone churn was 0.95%. The company recorded 65,000 Fios Internet net additions as high demand for reliable fiber optic broadband was spurred by higher video consumption. Verizon delivered 372,000 broadband net additions in the quarter. However, it registered 53,000 Fios Video net losses in the quarter, reflecting the ongoing shift from traditional linear video to over-the-top offerings.', 'score': 0.9967775, 'raw_content': None}], 'response_time': 1.52, 'request_id': 'f66109bf-d57d-415c-b14e-3ed310d7de95'}
